Installation on a headless server:

(See https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Install_Arch_Linux_via_SSH)

--- Insert Arch USB into USB
--- On a second USB drive, with FAT32, put all three files for a cloud-init setup
--- Boot device with both USB sticks inserted.
--- System will boot, and start ssh server and can be accessed over network
--- IP address needs to be found out, through DHCP server for example

(Tested with fitlet mini computer)